quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  18,84,"Surely, We gave him power on Earth and provided for him a way to everything."
  18,85,"So he followed a way,"
  18,86,"until when he reached where the sun sets, he found it setting into a miry spring and found near it a people. We said, "0 Dhul-Qarnain, either you punish or take to something good for them.""
  18,87,"He said, "As for the one who transgresses, we shall punish him, thereafter he will be returned to his Lord, and He will punish him - an evil punishment."
  18,88,"As for the one who believes and acts righteously, he will have the best in reward, and we shall deliver to him of our command that which is easy.""
  18,89,"Thereafter, he followed a way"
  18,90,"until he reached where the Sun rises; he found it rising over a people for whom We did not make any cover against it."
  18,91,"Thus it was. We encompassed in knowledge whatever he had with him."
  18,92,"Thereafter he followed a way"
  18,93,"until when he reached between the two mountains, he found on their hither side a people who did not seem to understand anything said."
  18,94,"They said, "0 Dhul-Qarnain, the Ya'juj and Ma'juj (Gog and Magog) are mischief-makers on the earth. So shall we set for you a revenue, provided that you make a barrier between us and them?""
  18,95,"He said, 'That which my Lord has placed under my control is better, so help me with strength and I shall make a rampart between you and them."
  18,96,"Bring me ingots of iron." (They proceeded accordingly) until when he leveled up (the gap) between the two mountain-sides, he said, "Blow." (They complied) until when he made it (like) fire, he said, 'Bring me molten copper and I will pour it upon this.""
  18,97,"So they (Ya'juj and Ma'juj) were not able to climb it, nor were they able to make a hole in it."